Longer ProcessWhen you‚Äôre living in the house, painting becomes more of a logistical challenge. You might need to paint one room at a time instead of finishing everything in one go, which can make the process drag out.

So, What‚Äôs the Best Choice?
It depends! If you have the time and opportunity, painting before moving in is usually the easiest and most efficient option. However, if you want to ensure the colors work well with your furniture and d√©cor, waiting until after move-in might be the smarter move.
Pro Tip: Hybrid Approach
